//! TODO-4 ceremony fixture — captured from a Samsung Galaxy S20+ 5G
//! (SM-G986U, Snapdragon 865, Android 13 / API 33, One UI 5.1, Knox 3.9)
//! on 2026-04-17 via dotwave's updated Kotlin ceremony with Gate 2
//! integrity-attestation production wired in.
//!
//! Contains every input the pallet-side `verify_binding_proof` consumes
//! for a complete end-to-end TODO-3 payload verification on real
//! hardware bytes.
//!
//! # Known dev-vs-prod caveats to resolve at pallet wiring time
//!
//! 1. **`signing_cert_hash` mismatch with `DOTWAVE_SIGNING_CERT_HASH`.**
//!    `zk-pki-integrity` still has the constant at `[0u8; 32]`
//!    placeholder. The blob carries the real dev-build hash, so
//!    `verify_integrity_attestation` currently rejects with
//!    `InvalidSigningCert`. Resolve by updating the constant to this
//!    captured value (dev-only) or by gating the check for tests.
//!
//! 2. **`package_name` vs `attestationApplicationId`.** Blob declares
//!    `"com.dotwave.app"` (production target), but the dev APK's
//!    `applicationId = "com.dotwave.dotwave"` — the Keystore daemon
//!    baked that into the chain's `attestationApplicationId` extension.
//!    The TODO-4 pallet cross-check step will need to account for this
//!    dev/prod divergence.

